version_description: My version has corrected chords for the intro, chorus, bridge, and outro. Also, the chords are better placed over the lyrics. My version also keeps the chords in the same context (G#m to F#, not Abm to F#. Although there is enharmonic equivalence, the technicality of the writing is incorrect.).
Can clearly hear that the introduction is correct, which is the part i'm most worried about. But is better than the other one in many ways.
The original is a little harder, so I made this easier version, enjoy:).
It has the intro, I tabbed myself, and chords adapted to the capo (It can be played without capo).
Easier for higher voices to sing with, simplified chords.
My version has corrections for the verse, bridge, and ending.
Version of the song from the Sleepers video short: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9I-mCaimqhk.
My version has corrections for the intro, verse, and bridge.  Also, the spacing of the chords over the lyrics and overall layout is better.

Really tried to aim for accuracy here. The things that most other tabs seemed to be missing out on were the E major in the intro, and the A diminished throughout the song. This is in the original key, btw. The chord changes are a little difficult in the verses, but if you know the song well enough you should be able to place them.
Other one is missing chords/different chords.
Other one has wrong chords in places, especially the bridge.
This tab is based off of this video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=W42dtL7-8DM. The strumming patterns were put in the tab, to try to make it a little easier to understand. :).
It is formatted nicely and gives the chords up top.
